 due in large measure to the designs of Urban and Bel Geddes. Together they were responsible for creating what has been called the “Golden Age” of American culture.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aDesignzUnited StatesxHistoryy20th century. 0aTheatersxStage-setting and sceneryzUnited StatesxHistoryy20th century. 7aDESIGN / Textile & Costume.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYale University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013z978311053799440uhttps://doi.org/10.12987/978030012955740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300129557423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780300129557/original  a978-3-11-053799-4  Yale University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles